Veteran ANC politician Zola Skweyiya passed away on Wednesday morning after a short illness The former Minister of Public Service and Administration and Minister of Social Development died at the age of 75. READ MORE: When the ANC dies, we must bury it – Phosa The politician died in Kloof Hospital in Pretoria on Wednesday morning, confirmed Mpho Mosimane, who was the spokesperson for the group of 101 stalwarts and apartheid activists who had asked last year for Jacob Zuma to step down. Mosimane said they would issue a statement later in the day. – News24